                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2744.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-06T13:00:00-07:04">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Orozco elected governor by State congress. No action taken with reference to
                    secession. Remarkable change in the situation within a few hours, undoubtedly
                    attributable to fear of intervention; prospects rather more favorable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
